  "doc_id": "45900",
  "text": "We have obtained the bacterial proteomes of all the B. animalis subsp. lactis strains whose genomes are completely sequenced and available at the National Center for Biotechnology Information (NCBI) servers (Table 1 ). All the sequence data used in this study were retrieved from the BioProject collection of the NCBI, using the public FTP site (ftp://ftp.ncbi.nih.gov/genomes/bacteria/) [CITATION_1] . Peptidomes were basically obtained through the following pipeline: i) retrieval of proteins encoded in the publicly available and completely sequenced genomes, ii) in silico digestion of proteins using human gut endopeptidases, and iii) comparison of the peptides according to their theoretical mass (peaks) and subsequent computation of consensus peak sets.",
